<item>
            <title>[BOOKKEEPER-74] Bookkeeper Persistence Manager should give up topic on error</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-74</link>
                <project id="12311293" key="BOOKKEEPER">Bookkeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are a couple of problematic cases to deal with:&lt;br/&gt;
i)Other region is pushing messages faster that my bookkeeper can handle it (unlikely, but we should have an answer for&lt;br/&gt;
this setting)&lt;br/&gt;
ii) If there is an error from BK while persisting messages, we cannot continue (because the ordering gurantee might be&lt;br/&gt;
violated). In this case, the BK layer should give up the topic.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To retain ordering guarantees, this should be done below the Region manager in the persistence manager layer&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
